#ROOMS
#9600
The Tower Gates~
A series of intricate iron gates stand here before you.  The clouds that
roll across the infinite skies are a deep violet, contrasting the dark blue
heavens, which were once clear as a summers day.  Beyond the gates you can
see a very elabourate garden, all sorts of floura and fauna kept within the
towers gates.  The scenery within is a stark difference to what is behind
you, rocky crags, mountainous peaks, very bleak and forboding.  The tower
before you seems to stretch on forever ...  
 
You see a sign here, sitting in the wet soil.
It reads as follows:
 
"Do not proceed any further, for your own sake. This is a true 
testing ground for the l337.  Only enter here if you truly feel you
have what it takes.  The things here WILL kick your ass.  If you're feelin
froggy then leap boys and girls. If not, back your ass up, this isn't 
for little kids.
 
-- Ishamael Bgreathiou
Building a Better Wyrm. Building a Better You.
~
0 8201 1
D0
~
~
0 0 9601
D3
~
~
0 0 9961
S
#9601
The Gardens of Bgreathiou~
The gates swing shut behind you, and you realize that there is no turning
back for you.  The sweet scent of honeydew and nightshade fill your
nostrils, and all around is serenity and calm.  Large trees shade you from
the sunlight, which is steadily fading, and keep the harsh winds off of your
face.  Tendrils of strange plants snake into the walkway, coiling up like
serpents.  The pathway continues on in the only fashion it could take, up to
the door.  
~
0 8192 0
D0
~
~
0 0 9602
S
#9602
Edge of the Garden~
The gardens start to pan off into nothingness as you pass them by,
leaving behind only the faintest hint of their aroma.  Now all you see is
stone that extends into the very heavens, piercing the sky with its spire. 
The lights begin to fade, and all that illuminates this place are a pair of
eyes.  They flicker like fiery balls of protoplasm, contained within the
shell of something you cannot name.  It is grey, and has no sex or physical
features to speak of.  It tilts its head once and glares, informing you that
you have trespassed into the hold of the Great Archsorcerer Bgreathiou.  
~
0 8196 0
D0
~
~
0 0 9603
S
#9603
The Entrance to the Tower of Bgreathiou~
You now stand directly in front of the double wooden doors that lead into
the tower that stretches up into eternity.  The stones are all black, not
charred but black as night nonetheless.  You can hear screams of anguish on
the wind, cries of mercy and begging of forgiveness fill the ears of all who
come here.  The skies turn black as well, and bolts of lightning sizzle into
the ground, but they are green and acidic instead of white hot bolts of
lightning that you are familiar with.  
~
