#9609
The Keep of Ultan Bgreathiou~
Stretched out before you is a strange looking room, built over the top of
the dungeon crypt.  The walls are charred black, save the spots of blood
tainting the smooth surface.  A strange symbol was carved into the ground,
and from it large columns of sickly green flames burst at almost random
intervals.  A throne rests in the far end of this room, and for once it is
empty.  Chained to the walls however are creatures of unknown origins, whose
bodies look as though they were patched together, a conglomerate of pain and
suffering swirls in these mad beasts eyes.  The chains snap quickly as they
froth and foam at the mouth, lunging, thirsting for blood.  
~
