#9656
The Bedchamber of Ishamael and Yvonne Bgreathiou~
You have entered the chambers of the Master, but he is not in them. 
Sitting upon the bed is a tall pale woman garbed in a snug black dress.  The
room is larger than all the rest, and decoarated with banners of all sorts
of nations, swords of conquered kings, and gems of all sizes and shapes. 
This room is a shrine to debauchery itself, in all of its splendor.  The
only apparant light comes from a balcony, the violet clouds swirling
absently in the skies.  
~
