#9661
The Torture Chambers~
The hollow screams you heard in the halls return, much more lively here. 
A man stands amongst a rack of weapons, but instead of picking them out for
usage, he is impaling himself upon spears, jagged knives and thorned whips. 
His eyes look dead and lost, and he writhes upon the cross of blades he
himself forged wordlessly.  When you ponder just why he does not scream out
you realize that his eyes have been taken away, and his voice box was cut
out, lips sewn together to prevent a word ever emitting him.  Underneath a
grate lies an altar of unknown origins, and down the hall are the prisoners
chambers.  
~
