#9662
A sacrificial Altar~
An altar stands here, extending fifteen feet into the air.  It seems to
almost be made of the same stone as the ground and walls around you, shaped
into existance without the touch of mans tools.  It drips ichor and blood,
and that fire is here as well, dancing along the altar, and the circle of
black sand that surrounds it.  This room is dead silent, save the crackling
of flames, but only for a moment.  The sound of a dull, throaty chant fills
your ears, the names and words used completely foreign ...  
~
